20/08/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- On Tuesday (19 August), the government received a preliminary response from the US administration to a questionnaire regarding the US request for the deployment of Turkish peacekeepers in Iraq.
Ankara had sought specifics about the number of soldiers requested, where they would be deployed and what their mission would be.
Refusing to reveal details of the US response, Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said only that the government would continue to evaluate the request before making a decision.
(Radikal, Hurriyet - 20/08/03;
Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 19/08/03)
